laboratory_examinations.findings: The abdomen shows a fluid-filled appendix measuring 8 mm at its tip with a 1.6 x 1.8 cm rim enhancing fluid collection at the base. Multiple bilateral cortical renal hypo densities noted, with the largest measuring approximately 6 mm. No hydronephrosis, no intrahepatic biliary duct dilation, and the liver shows homogeneous attenuation without focal lesion.
Valuestr: 9.7 mg/dL; NO GROWTH (indicating perhaps a culture result). Reference range: 8.4 - 10.3.
